$$ How to take a list input in Elang
say("Enter some numbers separated by commas: ").newl
raw = take("> ")

$$ 1. Split by comma (returns list of strings)
items = raw.split(",")
say("Raw strings: ").space
say(items).newl

$$ 2. Convert to numbers using .map() and a lambda
$$ Note: trim() is useful to remove accidental spaces around commas
nums = items.map(x => x.trim().to_int())

say("Actual numbers: ").space
say(nums).newl
say("Sum of numbers: ").space
say(nums.sum()).newl
